Sentencas: The composites consisted of oxygen ion conductive (La0.75Sr0.2Ba0.05)0.175Ce0.825O1.891 (LSBC) and proton conductive BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d (BZCY) prepared by solid state reaction and impregnation are sintered to form composite and phase gradient membranes, respectively.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The conductivity of (100-x)LSBC-xBZCY composite membranes exhibit non-ohmic in air and semiconductive diode behavior in Ar/5%H2 higher than 500 degrees C.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The elemental concentration gradient of Ba, Ce and O at grain boundaries of LSBC/BZCY corresponds to the inter-diffusion and Schottky barrier formation.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The Schottky barrier of dual phase boundary (DPB) may be beneficial for dual-ion conduction.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The microstructures of sintered and polished (100-x)LSBC-xBZCY surface exhibit convex hard LSBC and concave soft BZCY.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The percolated 70LSBC-30BZCY of the composite membrane obtains the power density of 20.51 mW/cm2.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The phase gradient membrane of BZCY impregnated LSBC presents the higher power density of 40.6 mW/cm2 (700 degrees C).
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: The new two-phase composite and phase gradient membranes generate more simple and compact layer structure than sandwiched solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell

Sentencas: Such two-phase dual-ion membranes provided by our economical process can be considered to develop new single membrane fuel cells possibly.
Titulo: Economical preparation and characterization of dual-ion conducting fuel cell
